24/05/2011
ATHENS, Greece -- The government decided on Monday (May 23rd) to proceed immediately with the sale of state stakes in the OTE telecoms company, Postbank, the ports of Thessaloniki and Piraeus and the Thessaloniki water company. 
Earlier this week, the EU urged authorities to accelerate the privatisation programme. 
Finance Minister George Papaconstantinou announced that the cabinet will continue with structural reforms in order to achieve the 7.5% deficit target for 2011. 
The government will discuss its midterm fiscal programme with the opposition Tuesday. 
(ANA-MPA, eKathimerini, BBC - 23/05/11)
